  "response_text": "# 7-Day Weight Loss Meal Plan\n\n## Principles\n- 1,500-1,800 calories/day (adjust based on your needs)\n- High protein, moderate carbs, healthy fats\n- Whole foods, minimal processed items\n- Plenty of water and fiber\n\n---\n\n## **MONDAY**\n- **Breakfast:** Egg white omelet (2 eggs) with spinach, whole wheat toast\n- **Lunch:** Grilled chicken breast, brown rice, steamed broccoli\n- **Snack:** Greek yogurt with berries\n- **Dinner:** Baked salmon, sweet potato, green beans\n\n## **TUESDAY**\n- **Breakfast:** Oatmeal with banana and almonds\n- **Lunch:** Turkey and veggie wrap, side salad\n- **Snack:** Apple with almond butter\n- **Dinner:** Lean ground turkey tacos (lettuce wraps), black beans\n\n## **WEDNESDAY**\n- **Breakfast:** Greek yogurt parfait with granola and fruit\n- **Lunch:** Tuna salad with mixed greens\n- **Snack:** Celery with hummus\n- **Dinner:** Grilled chicken, quinoa, roasted vegetables\n\n## **THURSDAY**\n- **Breakfast:** Veggie scramble with whole grain toast\n- **Lunch:** Lentil soup, side salad\n- **Snack:** Berries and cottage cheese\n- **Dinner:** Baked white fish, wild rice, asparagus\n\n## **FRIDAY**\n- **Breakfast:** Smoothie (protein powder, spinach, berries, almond milk)\n- **Lunch:** Grilled chicken bowl with vegetables and brown rice\n- **Snack:** String cheese and grapes\n- **Dinner:** Lean beef stir-fry with broccoli and brown rice\n\n## **SATURDAY**\n- **Breakfast:** Whole grain pancakes with fruit\n- **Lunch:** Chickpea salad with cucumber and tomato\n- **Snack:** Mixed nuts (small portion)\n- **Dinner:** Turkey meatballs with zucchini noodles and marinara\n\n## **SUNDAY**\n- **Breakfast:** Scrambled eggs with mushrooms and whole wheat toast\n- **Lunch:** Baked chicken breast, sweet potato, Brussels sprouts\n- **Snack:** Pear and almonds\n- **Dinner:** Vegetable soup, grilled lean steak, side salad\n\n---\n\n## **Tips for Success**\n✓ Drink 8+ glasses of water daily\n✓ Prep meals in advance\n✓ Use smaller plates\n✓ Eat slowly and mindfully\n✓ Include regular exercise\n✓ Get adequate sleep\n✓ Track your intake\n\n**Important:** Consult a doctor or registered dietitian before starting any weight loss plan, especially if you have health conditions.",
